article.headline: Booker scores 19, balanced No. 11 Texas women top Oklahoma State 76-66 for 1,200 win

images.name: Oklahoma State Cowgirls vs. Texas Longhorns - Game Highlights
images.caption: Watch the Game Highlights from Oklahoma State Cowgirls vs. Texas Longhorns, 01/20/2024

article.linkText: Booker scores 19, balanced No. 11 Texas women top Oklahoma State 76-66 for 1,200 win
article.story: STILLWATER, Okla. -- — Freshman Madison Booker scored 14 of her 19 points in the second half, Taylor Jones had a double double, and No. 11 Texas pulled away for a 76-66 win over Oklahoma State on Saturday, the 1,200th win for the Longhorns' program. Up four entering the fourth quarter, the Longhorns scored the first eight points and outscored the Cowgirls 19-13. Jones had 18 points and 14 rebounds, Aaliyah Moore had 17 points and eight rebounds and Shaylee Gonzales had 15 points for Texas (18-2, 5-2 Big 12). Booker had six rebounds, five assists and five steals. Anna Greta Asi scored 22 points for the Cowgirls (11-7, 4-3) on 8-of-10 shooting, hitting two 3-pointers in the last minute. Hannah Gusters added 14 points and Lior Garzon had 11. Gonzales, Booker and Jones had layups to open the final period and Booker's two free throws made it 65-53. The lead stayed in double figures the rest of the way as Oklahoma State went 4 of 14 in the fourth quarter. Texas made 14 of 24 shots in the second half and shot 53% and 17 of 21 from the foul line. OSU made 7 3s and shot 43%. Jones and Gonzales combined for 22 points on 9-of-13 shooting to help Texas take a 39-30 lead at the half. The Longhorns were plus-5 in rebounding and turned 11 turnovers into 14 points. The 12-4 advantage in second-chance points and 7-of-9 free throw shooting compared to 1 of 4 was the difference. A three-point play by Shay Holles to start start an 8-0 run that Jones ended with a three-point play, gave Texas a 14-5 lead. Only once after that did the Cowgirls get it down to a one possession game before the break. Booker scored the first basket of the second half to put Texas on top 41-30, but Quincy Noble scored the first seven Oklahoma State points and Asi had a seven-point run. Asi's 3-pointer tied the game at 45 with about 5 1/2 minutes to go. The Longhorns scored the next six and had a 47-33 lead entering the fourth quarter. Texas is at home against Oklahoma and Oklahoma State is at Cincinnati on Wednesday. ------ Get alerts and updates on AP Top 25 basketball throughout the season.
